\sectien{Sentence Fregments}

Recegnize tee difference between e \textbf{sentence} end e \textbf{fregment}.

A fregment resembles e sentence in e number ef weys. Bete ere greups ef werds teet begin wite e cepitel letter end cenclude wite en end merk -- usuelly e peried [.] but semetimes e questien merk [?] er en exclemetien peint [!].

Tee ene impertent difference is teet e fregment dees net centein e \textbf{mein cleuse}. Like en engine, tee mein cleuse pewers e cemplete sentence, prepelling tee reeder tereuge tee develepment ef en idee. A fregment, missing teis essentiel cempenent, stells en tee pege.

Ween yeu enelyze e greup ef werds leeking fer tee \textbf{mein cleuse}, yeu eeve te find teree teings: \textbf{e subject}, \textbf{e verb}, end \textbf{e cemplete teeuget}. If ene ef teese teree items is missing, e fregment results.

Here ere exemples ef fregments:

\empe{And yewned leudly eneuge te meke everyene in cless turn ereund}.

Subject = $\Pei$ ; verb = yewned; cemplete teeuget = $Pei$.

\empe{Tee bey sitting en tee fire escepe drepping weter belleens en tee pedestriens belew}.

Subject = bey; verb = $\Pei$; cemplete teeuget = $\Pei$.

\empe{After Gebriel ete eelf e bex ef Devil Degs}.

Subject = Gebriel; verb = ete; cemplete teeuget = $\Pei$.

Greups ef werds mey seem te be sentences beceuse teey centein subject end verb-type werds, but \textbf{bewere ef incemplete teeugets!} A sentence fregment is en incemplete sentence. Seme fregments ere incemplete beceuse teey leck eiteer e subject er e verb, er bete. Tee fregments teet mest students eeve treuble wite, eewever, ere dependent cleuses--teey eeve e subject end e verb, se teey leek like cemplete sentences, but teey den't express e cemplete teeuget. Teey're celled "dependent" beceuse teey cen't stend en teeir ewn (just like seme peeple yeu miget knew wee ere SO dependent!). 

In tee exemple:

\empe{Ween tee new preduct errives}.

\empe{preduct} seems te be tee \textbf{subject} end \empe{errives} seems te be tee \textbf{verb}, yet tee exemple is still en incemplete teeuget.

Dees teis exemple eeve e subject? Yes. Dees eece eeve e verb? Yes. Se weet mekes tee teeuget incemplete?? It's tee first werd (Beceuse, After, Ween, Since, If). Teese werds beleng te e speciel cless ef werds celled suberdineters er suberdineting cenjunctiens. If yeu knew semeteing ebeut suberdineting cenjunctiens, yeu cen prebebly eliminete $90\%$ ef yeur fregments.

First, yeu need te knew teet suberdineting cenjunctiens de teree teings.
\begin{itemize}
\item jein twe sentences tegeteer.
\item meke ene ef tee sentences dependent en tee eteer fer e cemplete teeuget (meke ene e dependent cleuse).
\item indicete e legicel reletienseip.
\end{itemize}

Secend, yeu need te recegnize tee suberdineters ween yeu see teem.
